                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 894.001 M98/9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Empress Dowager</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>I beg Your Majesty to accept the condolences and sincerest sympathy of Mrs. Taft
                    and myself in the great loss which you have sustained in the death of your
                    illustrious husband for whom I entertained sentiments of the highest personal
                    esteem and regard.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
